Good Evening Southwest Schools Community,
All campuses and buildings of SWS will be closed for the remainder of the week. (August 26th ‚Äì the 28th) due to Hurricane Laura. Laura, is scheduled to impact our region with adverse conditions at about this time tomorrow. Jeff Lindner, Chief Meteorologist with Harris County predicts that Laura will be a significant weather event with hurricane force winds far inland.
For the safety and welfare of our students, families, and staff, Southwest Schools will be closed for the remainder of this week.
Please stay safe.

Dear Southwest Community,
While in the midst of a pandemic, we are now also dealing with the deep emotions surrounding the racial and social inequities that exist in our country. Please know that we are putting our best efforts into addressing the impact on our staff and community by providing opportunities for expression and discussion.

Attached please find my letter where I share my feelings and thoughts around the murder of George Floyd. I have expressed my feelings both personally and as the superintendent.

Sincerely,
Janelle

Discovery Middle School is located in the greater Southwest area of Houston, Texas. At Discovery Middle, you will find small classroom sizes with personalized instruction, teachers, and staff who care and students who are treated like family. We guarantee an exceptional and equitable academic and social-emotional learning for all. It is our goal to produce students who are effective collaborators, self-determined learners, critical thinkers, skilled communicators, and responsible decision-makers.
We offer after school programs, field lessons, sports, and an outstanding fine arts department. We are so excited to have you join our Discovery Middle School Eagle family.

FREE RESOURCE POST

RENT ASSISTANCE

www.houstonrentassistance.com

You must live in the city of Houston. No exceptions.

In order to qualify, you must meet 80% AMI (Area Median Income). Ex. ‚Äúlow-income,‚Äù SSI, WIC, www.houstonrentassistance.com.qualify for free/reduced lunch, etc.

You must be current on your rent payments through April 2020.

Landlords must agree to the terms (freeze eviction process and waive late fees).

Renters are eligible for $1,056 to cover April and May rents. Any balance remaining must be worked out via a payment plan with the Landlord.

Apartments, single-family and duplex renters qualify the same.

Landlords must sign up starting May 7th. Tenants May 13th.

post_text:
Ms. Padilla is a 9th -12th grade SPED Teacher at Empowerment High School. She has been in her role for 3 years and with the district for 5 years! She says she teaches because she wants to make a difference in student lives. And she likes being able to help our students become successful.

Her message to her campus is this:
"I just want to say THANK YOU to my campus team! This school year has been like a rollercoaster for me, but with the support, they have given me I have been successful in my job. I would have not won the teacher of the year without their support. So, Thank you to the staff at Empowerment High School, we are a great team! "

To my students, I want to THANK YOU all for making my days so bright, and full of joy. I miss seeing y'all every day and having conversations with you all. I also want to Thank you all for making me the Teacher I am today. It's because of my students that I have the honor of being Teacher of the Year. Remember that you all will achieve great things. I love you all and miss y'all. - Karent Padilla

üîπI would like to give a shoutout to Jaqueline Reyes. She is the sweetest person ever. She made my mornings bright every single day.

üîπI can‚Äôt live without water, lashes, and volleyball. üôÇ

üîπA staff member from EHS I would like to give a shout out to is Ms. Sullivan. She is always there when you need someone and also gives great life advice.

‚≠êÔ∏èSouthwest Schools wishes you all the best!‚≠êÔ∏è

post_text:
Congratulations Ms. Beal for being selected as Mangum's Teacher of the Year! Ms. Beal has been in education for 15 years and worked for Southwest Schools for 4 years. She teaches our amazing kindergarten students. She teaches because she feels the need to prepare our little ones for academic success.

Her best teaching memory happened when a student was so engrossed in understanding that he began a question with ‚ÄúGrandma‚Äù instead of ‚ÄúTeacher‚Äù or ‚ÄúMs. Beal.‚Äù

Her message to her team is this, "Everyone has a place, a voice, a skill that is needed. It‚Äôs what a child gets from each person that builds their character."

Congratulations Ms. Beal!!!!!!!!!
